CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper July 12, 1941, pg. 23, reads: "One of Five Deliveries Made in Past Week - Pictured above is George G. Hill of 532 Junilla street, who recently took delivery on a new Ford Sedan and Walter Petty, salesman for Steel City Motors, 3131 Forbes street, Ma. 8844.  This is one of five new car deliveries made by Mr. Petty last week.  Hill plans to use his new car for business as well as pleasure."
TitMainTitle: George G. Hill, Steel City Motors car salesman Walter Petty, and another man gathered in and around Ford car parked on Finland Street next to Robert E. Williams park, Upper Hill District
